Takealot has discounted several sought-after tech products as part of its early access app-exclusive deals leading up to its “Ultimate Checkout” sale. The Ultimate Checkout sale will start on 25 July and end on 27 July. There are several notable TV deals, like the TCL 43-inch FHD Android TV for R3,999 and Hisense’s 43-inch A4G for R4,899. Some deals also include a gift voucher from Takealot-owned Superbalist or Mr Delivery. For example, TCL’s 43-inch TV comes with a R450 Superbalist voucher, and buying the Philips 4300 Series Espresso Machine gives you a R1,000 Superbalist voucher. If you are shopping for a new Garmin smartwatch, you can grab the Fenix 6s for R8,299, while the Venu is discounted to R4,999. Apple fans can get a pair of AirPods Pro for R3,799, while a 13-inch M1 MacBook Air and an iPhone 13 with 128GB storage each cost R16,999. Acer’s Swift X 14-inch notebook with a Ryzen 5 processor, 8GB of RAM, and an Nvidia GTX 1650 is R12,999. Those who want a more powerful gaming laptop can get the MSI Bravo 15, featuring a Ryzen 5 5600H processor, a Radeon RX 5500M graphics card, 8GB RAM, and a 15.6-inch 144Hz display for R13,999. Other notable deals include the AOC Q34P2 34-inch monitor for R5,999 and the Huawei MatePad T10s tablet for R3,599. Below are some of the best early access deals on Takealot. These deals are only available while stocks last. <img class="size-full wp-image-453698 aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Xiaomi-Mi-3.5l-air-fryer.png" alt="" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Xiaomi-Mi-3.5l-air-fryer.png 800w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Xiaomi-Mi-3.5l-air-fryer-600x400.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Xiaomi-Mi-3.5l-air-fryer-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />